{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852649425,"sessionID":"ses_286ef44c2ffenDTTydtMZC8npT","part":{"id":"prt_d7910f0250010CcmijGBaRUU1n","messageID":"msg_d7910d8c80018ek1BCcPDxEjRC","sessionID":"ses_286ef44c2ffenDTTydtMZC8npT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8883aee36a2943199125b7c777a87fb0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: | Item | Value |\n5: |------|-------|\n6: | AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n7: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n8: | Language | Go |\n9: | Size | M |\n10: | Design | ST-1 |\n11: \n12: ## Task Checklist\n13: ### Phase 1: 核心数据结构 (ST-1)\n14: - [ ] **T1.1**: 定义 JWT 配置结构\n15:   - 创建 JWTConfig 结构体\n16:   - 支持从配置文件/环境变量读取\n17:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n18:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router`\n19: \n20: - [ ] **T1.2**: 定义 Claims 结构体\n21:   - 扩展 jwt.RegisteredClaims\n22:   - 添加自定义字段\n23:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n24:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router`\n25: \n26: ### Phase 2: JWT 服务实现 (ST-2)\n27: - [ ] **T2.1**: 实现 JWTService\n28:   - Sign 方法：签发 Token\n29:   - Verify 方法：验证 Token\n30:   - Refresh 方法：刷新 Token\n31:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n32:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTService -v`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T2.2**: 实现 KeyManager\n35:   - 支持 HS256 密钥管理\n36:   - 支持 RS256 密钥对管理\n37:   - 密钥加载与验证\n38:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n39:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManager -v`\n40: \n41: ### Phase 3: 认证中间件 (ST-3)\n42: - [ ] **T3.1**: 实现 AuthMiddleware\n43:   - Token 解析\n44:   - Token 验证\n45:   - Claims 注入上下文\n46:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware/auth.go`\n47:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router/middleware -run TestAuthMiddleware -v`\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T3.2**: 实现错误处理\n50:   - 统一错误响应格式\n51:   - 日志记录\n52:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware/auth.go`\n53:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router/middleware -run TestAuthErrors -v`\n54: \n55: ### Phase 4: 测试与文档 (ST-4)\n56: - [ ] **T4.1**: 单元测试\n57:   - JWTService 测试\n58:   - KeyManager 测试\n59:   - AuthMiddleware 测试\n60:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`, `pkg/router/middleware/auth_test.go`\n61:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router/... -cover`\n62: \n63: - [ ] **T4.2**: 集成测试\n64:   - 完整认证流程测试\n65:   - 刷新流程测试\n66:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n67:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestIntegration -v`\n68: \n69: ## Task Dependencies\n70: ```\n71: T1.1 ──┬── T2.1 ──┬── T3.1 ── T4.1\n72:        │          │\n73: T1.2 ──┴── T2.2 ──┴── T3.2 ── T4.2\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ## Verification Commands\n77: | Task | Verification Command |\n78: |------|----------------------|\n79: | T1.1, T1.2 | `go build ./pkg/router` |\n80: | T2.1 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTService -v` |\n81: | T2.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManager -v` |\n82: | T3.1 | `go test ./pkg/router/middleware -run TestAuthMiddleware -v` |\n83: | T3.2 | `go test ./pkg/router/middleware -run TestAuthErrors -v` |\n84: | T4.1 | `go test ./pkg/router/... -cover` |\n85: | T4.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestIntegration -v` |\n86: \n87: ## Acceptance Criteria\n88: - [ ] JWT Token 签发功能正常\n89: - [ ] Token 验证中间件正确拦截无效请求\n90: - [ ] Token 刷新机制工作正常\n91: - [ ] 支持 HS256 和 RS256 算法\n92: - [ ] 测试覆盖率 ≥ 80%\n93: - [ ] 所有验证命令通过\n94: \n95: ## Files Modified/Created\n96: | File | Status | Description |\n97: |------|--------|-------------|\n98: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | Created | JWT 核心功能实现 |\n99: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | Created | JWT 单元测试 |\n100: | `pkg/router/middleware/auth.go` | Created | 认证中间件 |\n101: | `pkg/router/middleware/auth_test.go` | Created | 中间件测试 |\n102: \n103: ## Notes\n104: - 使用 golang-jwt/jwt v5 作为基础库\n105: - 遵循 Go 标准项目布局\n106: - 注意线程安全性\n107: \n108: ## Implementation Timeline\n109: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n110: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n111: | Phase 1 | T1.1, T1.2 | Not Started | 0% |\n112: | Phase 2 | T2.1, T2.2 | Not Started | 0% |\n113: | Phase 3 | T3.1, T3.2 | Not Started | 0% |\n114: | Phase 4 | T4.1, T4.2 | Not Started | 0% |\n\n(End of file - total 114 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | ST-1 |\n\n## Task Checklist\n### Phase 1: 核心数据结构 (ST-1)\n- [ ] **T1.1**: 定义 JWT 配置结构\n  - 创建 JWTConfig 结构体\n  - 支持从配置文件/环境变量读取\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router`\n\n- [ ] **T1.2**: 定义 Claims 结构体","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775852649393,"end":1775852649423}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852649428,"sessionID":"ses_286ef44c2ffenDTTydtMZC8npT","part":{"id":"prt_d7910f3e6001n8TRquUlsOd6V6","messageID":"msg_d7910d8c80018ek1BCcPDxEjRC","sessionID":"ses_286ef44c2ffenDTTydtMZC8npT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-24a48f1f0d394dc0ab84038b7167a946","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The Router JWT module provides token-based authentication for secure communication between Router and sandbox pods. It handles JWT token generation (signing), verification (validation), key management, and integration with the reverse proxy for Authorization header injection.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n23: │   Client SDK    │────▶│     Router      │────▶│   Sandbox Pod   │\n24: │ (Python/CLI)    │     │  (pkg/router)   │     │ (with picod)    │\n25: └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n26:                                │                         │\n27:                                │                         │\n28:                                ▼                         ▼\n29:                          ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n30:                          │   JWT Manager   │     │   Kubernetes    │\n31:                          │ (RS256 keys)    │     │   Secret Store  │\n32:                          └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ### JWT Token Flow\n36: \n37: ```\n38: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n39: │                    JWT Generation Flow                               │\n40: │                                                                      │\n41: │  1. Request arrives at handleInvoke (server.go)                     │\n42: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐       │\n43: │                                                               │       │\n44: │  2. SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession → SandboxInfo         │       │\n45: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n46: │                                                               │       │\n47: │  3. Check kind == SandboxKind or SandboxClaimKind            │       │\n48: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n49: │                                                               │       │\n50: │  4. JWTManager.GenerateToken(claims)                         │       │\n51: │     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │       │\n52: │     │  Claims:                                         │     │       │\n53: │     │  - session_id: sandbox.SessionID                 │     │       │\n54: │     │  - sandbox_id: sandbox.SandboxID                 │     │       │\n55: │     │  - namespace: sandbox.SandboxNamespace           │     │       │\n56: │     │  - name: sandbox.SandboxName                     │     │       │\n57: │     │  - exp: now + 5min                               │     │       │\n58: │     │  - iat: now                                      │     │       │\n59: │     │  - iss: \"agentcube-router\"                       │     │       │\n60: │     └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │       │\n61: │                                                               │       │\n62: │  5. RS256 Signing (rsa.PrivateKey)                           │       │\n63: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n64: │                                                               │       │\n65: │  6. ReverseProxyWrapper.Director                             │       │\n66: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤       │\n67: │     │  req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+jwt)        │       │\n68: │                                                               │       │\n69: │  7. Request forwarded to sandbox pod                         │       │\n70: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       │\n71: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### JWT Verification Flow (Future Enhancement)\n75: \n76: ```\n77: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n78: │                    JWT Verification Middleware                       │\n79: │                                                                      │\n80: │  HTTP Request with Authorization header                              │\n81: │        │                                                             │\n82: │        ▼                                                             │\n83: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n84: │  │ JWTAuthMiddleware                                             │   │\n85: │  │  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  │   │\n86: │  │  │   Extract      │──│   Parse        │──│   Validate     │  │   │\n87: │  │  │   Token        │  │   Claims       │  │   Signature    │  │   │\n88: │  │  └────────────────┘  └────────────────┘  └────────────────┘  │   │\n89: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n90: │        │                                                             │\n91: │        ▼                                                             │\n92: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n93: │  │ Claim Extraction → context.Set(\"session_id\", ...)             │   │\n94: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n95: │        │                                                             │\n96: │        ▼                                                             │\n97: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n98: │  │ Handler proceeds with authenticated context                    │   │\n99: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n100: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## Design\n106: \n107: ### Component Relationships\n108: \n109: | Component | Role | Dependencies |\n110: |-----------|------|--------------|\n111: | `JWTManager` | RS256 key generation, token signing, key persistence | `rsa.PrivateKey`, Kubernetes client (optional) |\n112: | `JWTConfig` | JWT configuration (expiration, issuer, algorithm) | None |\n113: | `JWTAuthMiddleware` | Token verification middleware (future) | `JWTManager` |\n114: | `TokenRefresher` | Token refresh handler (future) | `JWTManager` |\n115: | `KeyManager` | Key persistence to Kubernetes Secret | `JWTManager`, Kubernetes client |\n116: \n117: ### Dependencies\n118: \n119: | Package | Purpose | Import Path |\n120: |---------|---------|-------------|\n121: | golang-jwt | JWT token generation and parsing | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` |\n122: | crypto/rsa | RSA key generation and signing | Go standard library |\n123: | crypto/x509 | Key serialization (PKCS1, PKIX) | Go standard library |\n124: | encoding/pem | PEM encoding for key storage | Go standard library |\n125: | crypto/rand | Secure random key generation | Go standard library |\n126: | Kubernetes client | Secret persistence (optional) | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` |\n127: | Klog | Logging | `k8s.io/klog/v2` |\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## Data Structures\n132: \n133: ### JWTManager (`jwt.go`)\n134: \n135: ```go\n136: type JWTManager struct {\n137:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey  // 2048-bit RSA private key for signing\n138:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey   // Derived public key for verification\n139:     k8sClient  kubernetes.Interface  // Optional: for secret persistence\n140: }\n141: \n142: const (\n143:     rsaKeySize         = 2048                 // RSA key size in bits\n144:     jwtExpiration      = 5 * time.Minute      // Default token expiration\n145:     IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"  // Kubernetes Secret name\n146:     PrivateKeyDataKey  = \"private.pem\"        // Secret data key for private key\n147:     PublicKeyDataKey   = \"public.pem\"         // Secret data key for public key\n148: )\n149: \n150: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\"  // Overridden by AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ### JWTConfig (Future Enhancement)\n154: \n155: ```go\n156: type JWTConfig struct {\n157:     Algorithm      string        // \"RS256\" (default) or \"HS256\"\n158:     TokenExpiry    time.Duration // Default: 5 minutes\n159:     RefreshExpiry  time.Duration // Default: 30 minutes (for refresh tokens)\n160:     Issuer         string        // Default: \"agentcube-router\"\n161:     Audience       []string      // Optional audience claim\n162:     ClockSkew      time.Duration // Allowed clock skew for validation\n163: }\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ### JWT Claims Structure\n167: \n168: ```go\n169: type RouterClaims struct {\n170:     SessionID  string `json:\"session_id\"`  // Unique session identifier\n171:     SandboxID  string `json:\"sandbox_id\"`  // Sandbox pod identifier\n172:     Namespace  string `json:\"namespace\"`   // Kubernetes namespace\n173:     Name       string `json:\"name\"`        // Sandbox name\n174:     jwt.RegisteredClaims\n175: }\n176: \n177: type RegisteredClaims struct {\n178:     ExpiresAt *jwt.NumericDate `json:\"exp,omitempty\"`  // Expiration timestamp\n179:     IssuedAt  *jwt.NumericDate `json:\"iat,omitempty\"`  // Issued at timestamp\n180:     NotBefore *jwt.NumericDate `json:\"nbf,omitempty\"`  // Not valid before\n181:     Issuer    string           `json:\"iss,omitempty\"`  // \"agentcube-router\"\n182:     Subject   string           `json:\"sub,omitempty\"`  // Optional subject\n183:     Audience  ClaimStrings     `json:\"aud,omitempty\"`  // Optional audience\n184:     ID        string           `json:\"jti,omitempty\"`  // JWT ID (unique)\n185: }\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ### TokenPair (Future Enhancement)\n189: \n190: ```go\n191: type TokenPair struct {\n192:     AccessToken  string `json:\"access_token\"`   // Short-lived token (5 min)\n193:     RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\"`  // Long-lived token (30 min)\n194:     ExpiresIn    int64  `json:\"expires_in\"`     // Seconds until expiration\n195:     TokenType    string `json:\"token_type\"`     // Always \"Bearer\"\n196: }\n197: ```\n198: \n199: ### Key Persistence Types\n200: \n201: ```go\n202: type KeySecret struct {\n203:     Name      string            // Secret name: \"picod-router-identity\"\n204:     Namespace string            // Namespace from AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n205:     Data      map[string][]byte // \"private.pem\" and \"public.pem\" keys\n206: }\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ## API Contracts\n212: \n213: ### Existing: Token Generation (Internal)\n214: \n215: Token generation is performed internally during reverse proxy routing:\n216: \n217: ```go\n218: func (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n219: ```\n220: \n221: **Generated Claims:**\n222: ```json\n223: {\n224:   \"exp\": 1703001234,\n225:   \"iat\": 1703000934,\n226:   \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n227:   \"session_id\": \"sess-abc123\",\n228:   \"sandbox_id\": \"sbx-xyz789\",\n229:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n230:   \"name\": \"my-agent-runtime\"\n231: }\n232: ```\n233: \n234: ### Future: Token Issuance Endpoint\n235: \n236: | Method | Path | Description |\n237: |--------|------|-------------|\n238: | POST | `/auth/token` | Issue new access/refresh token pair |\n239: | POST | `/auth/refresh` | Refresh access token using refresh token |\n240: | GET | `/auth/public-key` | Retrieve public key for verification |\n241: \n242: ### Token Issuance Request/Response\n243: \n244: ```go\n245: type TokenRequest struct {\n246:     UserID   string                 `json:\"user_id\"`    // User identifier\n247:     Roles    []string               `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`  // Role claims\n248:     Metadata map[string]interface{} `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`  // Custom claims\n249: }\n250: \n251: type TokenResponse struct {\n252:     AccessToken  string `json:\"access_token\"`   // JWT access token\n253:     RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\"`  // JWT refresh token\n254:     ExpiresIn    int64  `json:\"expires_in\"`     // Expiration in seconds\n255:     TokenType    string `json:\"token_type\"`     // \"Bearer\"\n256: }\n257: \n258: type RefreshRequest struct {\n259:     RefreshToken string `json:\"refresh_token\"`  // Valid refresh token\n260: }\n261: \n262: type PublicKeyResponse struct {\n263:     PublicKey string `json:\"public_key\"`  // PEM-encoded public key\n264:     Algorithm string `json:\"algorithm\"`   // \"RS256\"\n265:     Issuer    string `json:\"issuer\"`      // \"agentcube-router\"\n266: }\n267: ```\n268: \n269: ### Middleware Integration\n270: \n271: ```go\n272: type JWTAuthMiddlewareConfig struct {\n273:     SkipPaths      []string      // Paths to skip auth (e.g., \"/health/*\")\n274:     TokenExtractor TokenExtractor // Custom token extraction function\n275:     KeyFunc        jwt.Keyfunc   // Key lookup function\n276: }\n277: \n278: type TokenExtractor func(r *http.Request) (string, error)\n279: \n280: func DefaultTokenExtractor(r *http.Request) (string, error) {\n281:     authHeader := r.Header.Get(\"Authorization\")\n282:     if authHeader == \"\" {\n283:         return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n284:     }\n285:     parts := strings.Split(authHeader, \" \")\n286:     if len(parts) != 2 || parts[0] != \"Bearer\" {\n287:         return \"\", ErrTokenInvalidFormat\n288:     }\n289:     return parts[1], nil\n290: }\n291: ```\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## Key Management\n296: \n297: ### Key Generation Strategy\n298: \n299: ```\n300: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n301: │                    Key Lifecycle                                     │\n302: │                                                                      │\n303: │  1. Router Startup                                                   │\n304: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐       │\n305: │                                                               │       │\n306: │  2. Check Kubernetes Secret existence                        │       │\n307: │     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │       │\n308: │     │  k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets().Get(ctx, name)     │     │       │\n309: │     └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │       │\n310: │                                                               │       │\n311: │  3a. Secret exists → Load existing keys                      │       │\n312: │      ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │       │\n313: │      │  loadPrivateKeyPEM(secret.Data[\"private.pem\"])   │    │       │\n314: │      │  publicKey = &privateKey.PublicKey               │    │       │\n315: │      └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │       │\n316: │                                                               │       │\n317: │  3b. Secret not exists → Generate new keys                   │       │\n318: │      ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │       │\n319: │      │  rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)              │    │       │\n320: │      │  encodePrivateKeyPEM, encodePublicKeyPEM         │    │       │\n321: │      └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │       │\n322: │                                                               │       │\n323: │  4. Store keys in Kubernetes Secret                          │       │\n324: │     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │       │\n325: │     │  k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets().Create(ctx, secret)│     │       │\n326: │     └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │       │\n327: │                                                               │       │\n328: │  5. JWTManager ready for token operations                    │       │\n329: │     └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       │\n330: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ### PEM Encoding Functions\n334: \n335: ```go\n336: func encodePrivateKeyPEM(key *rsa.PrivateKey) []byte {\n337:     return pem.EncodeToMemory(&pem.Block{\n338:         Type:  \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\",\n339:         Bytes: x509.MarshalPKCS1PrivateKey(key),\n340:     })\n341: }\n342: \n343: func encodePublicKeyPEM(key *rsa.PublicKey) []byte {\n344:     bytes, err := x509.MarshalPKIXPublicKey(key)\n345:     if err != nil {\n346:         return nil\n347:     }\n348:     return pem.EncodeToMemory(&pem.Block{\n349:         Type:  \"PUBLIC KEY\",\n350:         Bytes: bytes,\n351:     })\n352: }\n353: \n354: func loadPrivateKeyPEM(data []byte) (*rsa.PrivateKey, error) {\n355:     block, _ := pem.Decode(data)\n356:     if block == nil {\n357:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode PEM block\")\n358:     }\n359:     return x509.ParsePKCS1PrivateKey(block.Bytes)\n360: }\n361: ```\n362: \n363: ### Secret Structure\n364: \n365: ```yaml\n366: apiVersion: v1\n367: kind: Secret\n368: metadata:\n369:   name: picod-router-identity\n370:   namespace: ${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE:-default}\n371: type: Opaque\n372: data:\n373:   private.pem: <base64-encoded RSA private key>\n374:   public.pem: <base64-encoded RSA public key>\n375: ```\n376: \n377: ---\n378: \n379: ## Error Handling\n380: \n381: ### Custom Error Types (`errors.go`)\n382: \n383: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Code | Message | Condition |\n384: |------------|-------------|------|---------|-----------|\n385: | `JWTSigningError` | 500 | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | \"jwt signing failed\" | Token signing failure |\n386: | `JWTValidationError` | 401 | `JWT_VALIDATION_FAILED` | \"jwt validation failed\" | Token verification failure |\n387: | `JWTTokenExpiredError` | 401 | `JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED` | \"jwt token expired\" | Token past expiration |\n388: | `JWTTokenMissingError` | 401 | `JWT_TOKEN_MISSING` | \"jwt token missing\" | No Authorization header |\n389: | `JWTInvalidFormatError` | 401 | `JWT_INVALID_FORMAT` | \"invalid authorization header format\" | Malformed header |\n390: | `JWTKeyLoadError` | 500 | `JWT_KEY_LOAD_FAILED` | \"jwt key load failed\" | Key loading failure |\n391: \n392: ### Error Type Definitions\n393: \n394: ```go\n395: type JWTSigningError struct {\n396:     Err error\n397: }\n398: \n399: func (e *JWTSigningError) Error() string {\n400:     return \"jwt signing failed: \" + e.Err.Error()\n401: }\n402: \n403: func (e *JWTSigningError) Status() int { return 500 }\n404: func (e *JWTSigningError) Code() string { return \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\" }\n405: func (e *JWTSigningError) Message() string { return \"jwt signing failed\" }\n406: \n407: type JWTTokenExpiredError struct {\n408:     TokenID string\n409: }\n410: \n411: func (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Error() string {\n412:     return \"jwt token expired: \" + e.TokenID\n413: }\n414: \n415: func (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Status() int { return 401 }\n416: func (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Code() string { return \"JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED\" }\n417: func (e *JWTTokenExpiredError) Message() string { return \"jwt token expired\" }\n418: ```\n419: \n420: ### Error Response Format\n421: \n422: ```json\n423: {\n424:   \"error\": \"<message>\",\n425:   \"code\": \"<error code>\"\n426: }\n427: ```\n428: \n429: ### JWT Parsing Errors Mapping\n430: \n431: | jwt.Parse Error | Router Error |\n432: |------------------|--------------|\n433: | `jwt.ErrTokenExpired` | `JWTTokenExpiredError` |\n434: | `jwt.ErrTokenSignatureInvalid` | `JWTValidationError` |\n435: | `jwt.ErrTokenMalformed` | `JWTValidationError` |\n436: | `jwt.ErrTokenNotValidYet` | `JWTValidationError` |\n437: \n438: ---\n439: \n440: ## Testing Strategy\n441: \n442: ### Test Coverage Goals\n443: \n444: | Component | Coverage Target | Key Test Cases |\n445: |-----------|-----------------|----------------|\n446: | `jwt.go` | 80%+ | Key generation, token signing, claim merging, expiration, PEM encoding/decoding |\n447: | `middleware.go` (auth) | 90%+ | Token extraction, validation flow, error responses, path skipping |\n448: | `KeyManager` | 85%+ | Secret creation, key loading, key rotation |\n449: \n450: ### Unit Tests (`jwt_test.go`)\n451: \n452: | Test | Description |\n453: |------|-------------|\n454: | `TestNewJWTManager` | Verify RSA key generation (2048-bit) |\n455: | `TestJWTManagerGenerateToken` | Token generation with custom claims, verify claims present |\n456: | `TestJWTManagerTokenExpiration` | Verify exp claim is approximately 5 minutes from now |\n457: | `TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey` | Verify public key retrieval for verification |\n458: | `TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM` | PEM encoding contains \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\" |\n459: | `TestEncodePublicKeyPEM` | PEM encoding contains \"PUBLIC KEY\" |\n460: | `TestLoadPrivateKeyPEM` | Load PEM data back to RSA key, verify key equality |\n461: | `TestLoadPrivateKeyPEMInvalid` | Invalid PEM data returns error |\n462: | `TestJWTSigningError` | Error type methods (Error, Status, Code, Message) |\n463: \n464: ### Integration Test Scenarios\n465: \n466: | Scenario | Description |\n467: |----------|-------------|\n468: | Key persistence | Generate → Store in K8s Secret → Restart → Load existing keys |\n469: | Token flow | Generate token → Verify with public key → Extract claims |\n470: | Proxy integration | Request → JWT generated → Authorization header set → Forwarded |\n471: | Secret namespace | AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env override for Secret location |\n472: \n473: ### Test Utilities\n474: \n475: ```go\n476: type MockJWTManager struct {\n477:     GenerateFunc func(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n478:     VerifyFunc   func(tokenString string) (*RouterClaims, error)\n479:     PublicKey    *rsa.PublicKey\n480: }\n481: \n482: type MockKeyManager struct {\n483:     StoreFunc  func(ctx context.Context, privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey) error\n484:     LoadFunc   func(ctx context.Context) (*rsa.PrivateKey, error)\n485:     ExistsFunc func(ctx context.Context) (bool, error)\n486: }\n487: ```\n488: \n489: ### Benchmarks\n490: \n491: ```go\n492: func BenchmarkJWTGenerateToken(b *testing.B) {\n493:     jwtMgr, _ := NewJWTManager()\n494:     claims := map[string]interface{}{\n495:         \"session_id\": \"test-session\",\n496:         \"sandbox_id\": \"test-sandbox\",\n497:     }\n498:     b.ResetTimer()\n499:     for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {\n500:         jwtMgr.GenerateToken(claims)\n501:     }\n502: }\n503: \n504: func BenchmarkJWTVerifyToken(b *testing.B) {\n505:     // Measure token verification performance\n506: }\n507: ```\n508: \n509: ---\n510: \n511: ## Implementation Checklist\n512: \n513: - [x] `JWTManager` struct with RSA 2048-bit key pair\n514: - [x] `GenerateToken(claims)` method with RS256 signing\n515: - [x] Standard claims: exp (5min), iat, iss (\"agentcube-router\")\n516: - [x] PEM encoding functions for private/public keys\n517: - [x] `GetPublicKey()` method for verification\n518: - [x] `JWTSigningError` custom error type\n519: - [ ] `ValidateToken(tokenString)` method for verification\n520: - [ ] `JWTAuthMiddleware` for incoming request authentication\n521: - [ ] Key persistence to Kubernetes Secret\n522: - [ ] Key rotation support\n523: - [ ] Token refresh endpoint\n524: - [ ] Public key distribution endpoint\n525: - [ ] Clock skew tolerance configuration\n526: \n527: ---\n528: \n529: ## Validation Rules\n530: \n531: 1. RSA key size must be 2048 bits (minimum for RS256 security)\n532: 2. Token expiration defaults to 5 minutes (short-lived for sandbox communication)\n533: 3. Issuer claim must be \"agentcube-router\" (hardcoded)\n534: 4. Private key stored in PKCS1 PEM format\n535: 5. Public key stored in PKIX PEM format\n536: 6. Secret name: `picod-router-identity`\n537: 7. Namespace: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env or `default`\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Security Considerations\n542: \n543: ### Key Storage\n544: - Private key stored in Kubernetes Secret (base64 encoded)\n545: - Secret should be mounted only in Router pod\n546: - Consider using sealed secrets for GitOps deployments\n547: \n548: ### Token Lifetime\n549: - Access tokens expire in 5 minutes (short-lived)\n550: - Tokens are single-use per request (forwarded to sandbox)\n551: - No token caching in Router\n552: \n553: ### Algorithm Security\n554: - RS256 preferred over HS256 (asymmetric, verifiable without secret)\n555: - Private key never shared with sandbox pods\n556: - Public key can be distributed to verification endpoints\n557: \n558: ### Key Rotation\n559: - Generate new keys: `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n560: - Store new keys in Secret with versioned name\n561: - Sandbox pods need updated public key for verification\n562: \n563: ---\n564: \n565: ## Open Questions\n566: \n567: 1. **Token Blacklist**: Should revoked sessions invalidate tokens immediately?\n568:    - Current: Tokens expire naturally after 5 minutes\n569:    - Alternative: Redis-backed blacklist for immediate revocation\n570: \n571: 2. **Multi-tenancy**: Should different namespaces use different keys?\n572:    - Current: Single key pair for all namespaces\n573:    - Alternative: Per-namespace key secrets\n574: \n575: 3. **Key Rotation Strategy**: When and how should keys rotate?\n576:    - Current: Keys generated once at startup\n577:    - Alternative: Scheduled rotation (weekly/monthly) with overlap period\n578: \n579: 4. **Token Audience**: Should tokens include audience claim?\n580:    - Current: No audience restriction\n581:    - Alternative: `aud: [\"sandbox-pod\"]` for target verification\n582: \n583: ---\n584: \n585: ## References\n586: \n587: - `jwt.go` — Current JWT implementation\n588: - `server.go:154-171` — Token generation in handleInvoke\n589: - `reverse_proxy.go:41-43` — Authorization header injection\n590: - `errors.go:63-81` — JWTSigningError definition\n591: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` — AuthModeType constants\n592: - [RFC 7519 — JSON Web Token (JWT)](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519)\n593: - [RFC 7518 — JSON Web Algorithms (JWA)](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7518)\n594: - [golang-jwt/jwt v5](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt)\n\n(End of file - total 594 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe Router JWT module provides token-based authentication for secure communication between Router and sandbox pods. It handles JWT token generation (signing), verification (validation), key management, and integration with the reverse proxy for Authorization header injection.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/design.md","time":{"start":1775852649396,"end":1775852649425}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852649429,"sessionID":"ses_286ef44c2ffenDTTydtMZC8npT","part":{"id":"prt_d7910f7b0001eSItHpmFhmaLOt","messageID":"msg_d7910d8c80018ek1BCcPDxEjRC","sessionID":"ses_286ef44c2ffenDTTydtMZC8npT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bf6796e41a4143349aad214243008476","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: | Item | Value |\n5: |------|-------|\n6: | AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n7: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n8: | Language | Go |\n9: | Size | M |\n10: | Stage | ST-0 |\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: 实现 Router 模块的 JWT 认证与签发功能，包括：\n14: - JWT Token 生成与签发\n15: - JWT Token 验证中间件\n16: - Token 刷新机制\n17: \n18: ## Out of Scope\n19: - OAuth2 集成\n20: - 第三方身份提供商对接\n21: - 用户权限管理（RBAC）\n22: \n23: ## Dependencies\n24: - 待分析\n25: \n26: ## Deliverables\n27: | File | Description |\n28: |------|-------------|\n29: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWT 核心功能实现 |\n30: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT 单元测试 |\n31: | `pkg/router/middleware/auth.go` | 认证中间件 |\n32: \n33: ## Acceptance Criteria\n34: - [ ] JWT Token 签发功能正常\n35: - [ ] Token 验证中间件正确拦截无效请求\n36: - [ ] Token 刷新机制工作正常\n37: - [ ] 测试覆盖率 ≥ 80%\n38: \n39: ## References\n40: - 待补充\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n## Metadata\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n实现 Router 模块的 JWT 认证与签发功能，包括：\n- JWT Token 生成与签发\n- JWT Token 验证中间件\n- Token 刷新机制\n\n## Out of Scope\n- OAuth2 集成\n- 第三方身份提供商对接","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/spec.md","time":{"start":1775852649398,"end":1775852649428}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852649432,"sessionID":"ses_286ef44c2ffenDTTydtMZC8npT","part":{"id":"prt_d7910fb9d001d7B9w5UB6XJpRi","messageID":"msg_d7910d8c80018ek1BCcPDxEjRC","sessionID":"ses_286ef44c2ffenDTTydtMZC8npT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-60bc126465994edca5d0272cc5418e9a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/jwt.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/jwt.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package router\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"crypto/rand\"\n6: \t\"crypto/rsa\"\n7: \t\"crypto/x509\"\n8: \t\"encoding/pem\"\n9: \t\"fmt\"\n10: \t\"os\"\n11: \t\"time\"\n12: \n13: \t\"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n14: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n15: )\n16: \n17: const (\n18: \trsaKeySize         = 2048\n19: \tjwtExpiration      = 5 * time.Minute\n20: \tIdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"\n21: \tPrivateKeyDataKey  = \"private.pem\"\n22: \tPublicKeyDataKey   = \"public.pem\"\n23: )\n24: \n25: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\"\n26: \n27: func init() {\n28: \tif ns := os.Getenv(\"AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\"); ns != \"\" {\n29: \t\tIdentityNamespace = ns\n30: \t}\n31: }\n32: \n33: type JWTManager struct {\n34: \tprivateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n35: \tpublicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n36: }\n37: \n38: func NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error) {\n39: \tprivateKey, err := rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, rsaKeySize)\n40: \tif err != nil {\n41: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate RSA key: %w\", err)\n42: \t}\n43: \n44: \treturn &JWTManager{\n45: \t\tprivateKey: privateKey,\n46: \t\tpublicKey:  &privateKey.PublicKey,\n47: \t}, nil\n48: }\n49: \n50: func (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error) {\n51: \tnow := time.Now()\n52: \n53: \ttokenClaims := jwt.MapClaims{\n54: \t\t\"exp\": now.Add(jwtExpiration).Unix(),\n55: \t\t\"iat\": now.Unix(),\n56: \t\t\"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n57: \t}\n58: \n59: \tfor k, v := range claims {\n60: \t\ttokenClaims[k] = v\n61: \t}\n62: \n63: \ttoken := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, tokenClaims)\n64: \n65: \ttokenString, err := token.SignedString(j.privateKey)\n66: \tif err != nil {\n67: \t\treturn \"\", &JWTSigningError{Err: err}\n68: \t}\n69: \n70: \treturn tokenString, nil\n71: }\n72: \n73: func (j *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error {\n74: \tklog.Warningf(\"not in cluster, skipping secret persistence\")\n75: \treturn nil\n76: }\n77: \n78: func encodePrivateKeyPEM(key *rsa.PrivateKey) []byte {\n79: \treturn pem.EncodeToMemory(&pem.Block{\n80: \t\tType:  \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\",\n81: \t\tBytes: x509.MarshalPKCS1PrivateKey(key),\n82: \t})\n83: }\n84: \n85: func encodePublicKeyPEM(key *rsa.PublicKey) []byte {\n86: \tbytes, err := x509.MarshalPKIXPublicKey(key)\n87: \tif err != nil {\n88: \t\treturn nil\n89: \t}\n90: \treturn pem.EncodeToMemory(&pem.Block{\n91: \t\tType:  \"PUBLIC KEY\",\n92: \t\tBytes: bytes,\n93: \t})\n94: }\n95: \n96: func loadPrivateKeyPEM(data []byte) (*rsa.PrivateKey, error) {\n97: \tblock, _ := pem.Decode(data)\n98: \tif block == nil {\n99: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode PEM block\")\n100: \t}\n101: \n102: \tkey, err := x509.ParsePKCS1PrivateKey(block.Bytes)\n103: \tif err != nil {\n104: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse private key: %w\", err)\n105: \t}\n106: \n107: \treturn key, nil\n108: }\n109: \n110: func (j *JWTManager) GetPublicKey() *rsa.PublicKey {\n111: \treturn j.publicKey\n112: }\n\n(End of file - total 112 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package router\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"crypto/rand\"\n\t\"crypto/rsa\"\n\t\"crypto/x509\"\n\t\"encoding/pem\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n\t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\trsaKeySize         = 2048\n\tjwtExpiration      = 5 * time.Minute\n\tIdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/jwt.go","time":{"start":1775852649401,"end":1775852649430}}}}
