{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852802920,"sessionID":"ses_286ef44c2ffenDTTydtMZC8npT","part":{"id":"prt_d791352f3001M7dTNpiyN4h2aD","messageID":"msg_d7911758a0018KuR56ya13OCz5","sessionID":"ses_286ef44c2ffenDTTydtMZC8npT","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-934a22d733cb4437b9013dbc167fb452","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md","content":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Data Structures (ST-1) ✓\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Define JWT constants in `jwt.go`\n  - `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n  - `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n  - `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n  - `PrivateKeyDataKey = \"private.pem\"`\n  - `PublicKeyDataKey = \"public.pem\"`\n  - `IdentityNamespace = \"default\"` (overridden by `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env)\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerTokenExpiration -v`\n\n- [x] **T1.2**: Define `JWTManager` struct in `jwt.go`\n  - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n  - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n\n- [x] **T1.3**: Define `JWTSigningError` in `errors.go`\n  - `Err error` field\n  - Implements `APIStatus` interface\n  - `Status() = 500`, `Code() = \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"`\n  - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTSigningError -v`\n\n### Phase 2: JWT Generation (ST-2) ✓\n\n- [x] **T2.1**: Implement `NewJWTManager()` constructor\n  - Generate RSA 2048-bit key: `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n  - Derive public key from private key\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n\n- [x] **T2.2**: Implement `GenerateToken(claims)` method\n  - Create JWT with standard claims: `exp` (now+5m), `iat` (now), `iss=\"agentcube-router\"`\n  - Merge custom claims into `jwt.MapClaims`\n  - Sign with RS256 algorithm\n  - Return signed token string or `JWTSigningError`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGenerateToken -v`\n\n- [x] **T2.3**: Implement PEM encoding helpers\n  - `encodePrivateKeyPEM(key)` - PKCS1 PEM encoding with \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\" block\n  - `encodePublicKeyPEM(key)` - PKIX PEM encoding with \"PUBLIC KEY\" block\n  - `loadPrivateKeyPEM(data)` - Parse PKCS1 PEM back to `*rsa.PrivateKey`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM -v`\n\n- [x] **T2.4**: Implement `GetPublicKey()` method\n  - Return `*rsa.PublicKey` for downstream verification\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey -v`\n\n- [x] **T2.5**: Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` placeholder\n  - Log warning \"not in cluster, skipping secret persistence\"\n  - Return nil (placeholder for future K8s Secret persistence)\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n\n### Phase 3: JWT Verification (ST-3)\n\n- [ ] **T3.1**: Define `RouterClaims` struct\n  - Extend `jwt.RegisteredClaims`\n  - Custom fields: `SessionID string`, `SandboxID string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`\n  - JSON tags: `session_id`, `sandbox_id`, `namespace`, `name`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n\n- [ ] **T3.2**: Define additional JWT error types in `errors.go`\n  - `JWTValidationError` - code `JWT_VALIDATION_FAILED`, HTTP 401\n  - `JWTTokenExpiredError` - code `JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED`, HTTP 401, field `TokenID`\n  - `JWTTokenMissingError` - code `JWT_TOKEN_MISSING`, HTTP 401\n  - `JWTInvalidFormatError` - code `JWT_INVALID_FORMAT`, HTTP 401\n  - `JWTKeyLoadError` - code `JWT_KEY_LOAD_FAILED`, HTTP 500\n  - All implement `APIStatus` interface\n  - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `ValidateToken(tokenString)` method\n  - Parse token with public key verification\n  - Map jwt library errors to custom error types\n  - Return `*RouterClaims` on success\n  - Handle: `jwt.ErrTokenExpired` → `JWTTokenExpiredError`\n  - Handle: `jwt.ErrTokenSignatureInvalid` → `JWTValidationError`\n  - Handle: `jwt.ErrTokenMalformed` → `JWTValidationError`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.4**: Implement JWT error mapping helper\n  - `mapJWTParseError(err)` function\n  - Convert `jwt` library errors to router custom errors\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMapJWTParseError -v`\n\n### Phase 4: Authentication Middleware (ST-4)\n\n- [ ] **T4.1**: Define `JWTAuthMiddlewareConfig` struct\n  - `SkipPaths []string` - paths to bypass auth (e.g., `/health/*`)\n  - `TokenExtractor TokenExtractor` - custom token extraction function\n  - `KeyFunc jwt.Keyfunc` - key lookup function\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n\n- [ ] **T4.2**: Define `TokenExtractor` function type\n  - `type TokenExtractor func(r *http.Request) (string, error)`\n  - Extract token from Authorization header or other sources\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n\n- [ ] **T4.3**: Implement `DefaultTokenExtractor(r)` function\n  - Get `Authorization` header from request\n  - Split by space, check format is \"Bearer <token>\"\n  - Return token string or `JWTTokenMissingError`/`JWTInvalidFormatError`\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultTokenExtractor -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `JWTAuthMiddleware(jwtMgr, config)` function\n  - Create Gin middleware for JWT verification\n  - Skip paths matching `config.SkipPaths`\n  - Extract token via `config.TokenExtractor` or `DefaultTokenExtractor`\n  - Validate token via `jwtMgr.ValidateToken`\n  - Inject claims into `gin.Context` via `c.Set(\"jwt_claims\", claims)`\n  - Return appropriate error response on validation failure\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuthMiddleware -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.5**: Implement error response formatting in middleware\n  - Use `APIStatus` interface for error details\n  - Return JSON: `{\"error\": \"<message>\", \"code\": \"<code>\"}`\n  - Set HTTP status code from `Status()` method\n  - Call `c.Abort()` to stop request processing\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuthMiddlewareErrors -v`\n\n- [ ] **T4.6**: Implement claims extraction helper `GetClaimsFromContext(c)`\n  - Retrieve claims from `gin.Context` via `c.Get(\"jwt_claims\")`\n  - Return `*RouterClaims` or nil if not present\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestGetClaimsFromContext -v`\n\n### Phase 5: Key Persistence (ST-5)\n\n- [ ] **T5.1**: Define `KeySecret` struct\n  - `Name string` - Secret name: `\"picod-router-identity\"`\n  - `Namespace string` - From `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE`\n  - `Data map[string][]byte` - Keys: `\"private.pem\"` and `\"public.pem\"`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n\n- [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `KeyManager` struct\n  - `k8sClient kubernetes.Interface`\n  - `namespace string`\n  - `secretName string`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n\n- [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `NewKeyManager(k8sClient)` constructor\n  - Read namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env or default to `\"default\"`\n  - Set `secretName = IdentitySecretName`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewKeyManager -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.4**: Implement `KeyManager.Exists(ctx)` method\n  - Check if Kubernetes Secret exists\n  - Call `k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets(namespace).Get(ctx, name, options)`\n  - Return `true` if exists, `false` if `IsNotFound` error\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerExists -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.5**: Implement `KeyManager.Load(ctx)` method\n  - Get Secret from Kubernetes\n  - Parse `secret.Data[\"private.pem\"]` via `loadPrivateKeyPEM`\n  - Return `*rsa.PrivateKey` or `JWTKeyLoadError`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerLoad -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.6**: Implement `KeyManager.Store(ctx, privateKey)` method\n  - Encode private key via `encodePrivateKeyPEM`\n  - Encode public key via `encodePublicKeyPEM`\n  - Create Kubernetes Secret with `Data` map\n  - Call `k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets(namespace).Create(ctx, secret, options)`\n  - Return error on failure\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerStore -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.7**: Update `JWTManager.TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` implementation\n  - Check if `k8sClient` is nil → skip (not in cluster)\n  - Call `KeyManager.Exists(ctx)`\n  - If exists: `KeyManager.Load(ctx)` → set private/public key\n  - If not exists: `KeyManager.Store(ctx, privateKey)` → persist new keys\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerKeyPersistence -v`\n\n### Phase 6: JWT Config (Optional) (ST-6)\n\n- [ ] **T6.1**: Define `JWTConfig` struct\n  - `Algorithm string` - default `\"RS256\"`, optional `\"HS256\"`\n  - `TokenExpiry time.Duration` - default `5 * time.Minute`\n  - `RefreshExpiry time.Duration` - default `30 * time.Minute`\n  - `Issuer string` - default `\"agentcube-router\"`\n  - `Audience []string` - optional\n  - `ClockSkew time.Duration` - default `30s`\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n\n- [ ] **T6.2**: Implement `DefaultJWTConfig()` function\n  - Return config with default values\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultJWTConfig -v`\n\n- [ ] **T6.3**: Update `NewJWTManager()` to accept optional `JWTConfig`\n  - `NewJWTManager(config *JWTConfig)` - nil config uses defaults\n  - Use config values for token expiration and issuer\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerWithConfig -v`\n\n### Phase 7: Unit Tests (ST-7)\n\n- [ ] **T7.1**: Add `ValidateToken` tests in `jwt_test.go`\n  - Test valid token verification\n  - Test expired token → `JWTTokenExpiredError`\n  - Test invalid signature → `JWTValidationError`\n  - Test malformed token → `JWTValidationError`\n  - Test token with custom claims extraction\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.2**: Add JWT error type tests in `errors_test.go`\n  - Test `JWTValidationError` implements `APIStatus`\n  - Test `JWTTokenExpiredError` implements `APIStatus`\n  - Test `JWTTokenMissingError` implements `APIStatus`\n  - Test `JWTInvalidFormatError` implements `APIStatus`\n  - Test `JWTKeyLoadError` implements `APIStatus`\n  - File: `pkg/router/errors_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.3**: Add middleware tests in `middleware_test.go`\n  - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with valid token\n  - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with invalid token\n  - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with missing token\n  - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with expired token\n  - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` skip paths\n  - Test `DefaultTokenExtractor` Bearer format\n  - Test `DefaultTokenExtractor` missing header\n  - Test `DefaultTokenExtractor` invalid format\n  - Test `GetClaimsFromContext` extraction\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuth -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.4**: Add KeyManager tests in `jwt_test.go`\n  - Test `NewKeyManager` constructor\n  - Test `KeyManager.Exists` with mock client\n  - Test `KeyManager.Load` with mock secret\n  - Test `KeyManager.Store` with mock client\n  - Test `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` integration\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManager -v`\n\n### Phase 8: Integration & Coverage (ST-8)\n\n- [ ] **T8.1**: Integration test for full JWT flow\n  - Generate token → Validate token → Extract claims\n  - Verify claims match original input\n  - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTIntegration -v`\n\n- [ ] **T8.2**: Integration test for middleware chain\n  - Request → JWTAuthMiddleware → Handler with claims access\n  - Verify 401 on invalid token\n  - Verify 200 with claims injection on valid token\n  - File: `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMiddlewareIntegration -v`\n\n- [ ] **T8.3**: Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n  - Run `go test ./pkg/router -cover`\n  - Identify uncovered code paths\n  - Add missing test cases\n  - File: `pkg/router/*_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -cover`\n\n- [ ] **T8.4**: All router tests pass\n  - `go test ./pkg/router -v`\n  - Fix any failing tests\n  - File: `pkg/router/*_test.go`\n  - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -v`\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\nPhase 1 (Completed)\n  T1.1 ── T1.2 ── T1.3\n     │\n     ▼\nPhase 2 (Completed)\n  T2.1 ── T2.2 ── T2.3 ── T2.4 ── T2.5\n     │\n     ▼\nPhase 3 (JWT Verification)\n  T3.1 ── T3.2 ──┬── T3.3 ── T3.4\n                │\nPhase 4 (Middleware) ────────────────────────────┘\n  T4.1 ── T4.2 ── T4.3 ── T4.4 ── T4.5 ── T4.6\n     │\n     ▼\nPhase 5 (Key Persistence)\n  T5.1 ── T5.2 ── T5.3 ── T5.4 ── T5.5 ── T5.6 ── T5.7\n     │\n     ▼\nPhase 6 (JWT Config - Optional)\n  T6.1 ── T6.2 ── T6.3\n     │\n     ▼\nPhase 7 (Unit Tests)\n  T7.1 ── T7.2 ── T7.3 ── T7.4\n     │\n     ▼\nPhase 8 (Integration & Coverage)\n  T8.1 ── T8.2 ── T8.3 ── T8.4\n```\n\n---\n\n## Verification Commands\n\n| Task | Verification Command |\n|------|----------------------|\n| T1.1, T1.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v` |\n| T1.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTSigningError -v` |\n| T2.1, T2.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGenerateToken -v` |\n| T2.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM -v` |\n| T2.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey -v` |\n| T3.1 | `go build ./pkg/router/...` |\n| T3.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v` |\n| T3.3, T3.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v` |\n| T4.1, T4.2 | `go build ./pkg/router/...` |\n| T4.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultTokenExtractor -v` |\n| T4.4, T4.5, T4.6 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuthMiddleware -v` |\n| T5.1, T5.2, T5.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewKeyManager -v` |\n| T5.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerExists -v` |\n| T5.5 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerLoad -v` |\n| T5.6 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerStore -v` |\n| T5.7 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerKeyPersistence -v` |\n| T6.1 | `go build ./pkg/router/...` |\n| T6.2, T6.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTConfig -v` |\n| T7.1 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v` |\n| T7.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v` |\n| T7.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuth -v` |\n| T7.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManager -v` |\n| T8.1 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTIntegration -v` |\n| T8.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMiddlewareIntegration -v` |\n| T8.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -cover` |\n| T8.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -v` |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] JWT Token 签发功能正常 (T2.1-T2.4 completed)\n- [ ] `ValidateToken` 方法正确验证 Token (T3.3)\n- [ ] JWT 错误